==English==

===Noun===
'''[[deep]] [[vein]] [[thrombosis]]''' ''or'' '''[[deep]]-[[vein]] [[thrombosis]]''' (''uncountable'')

# {{pathology}} A potentially [[fatal]] [[condition]] in which one or more [[thrombus|thrombi]] (or [[clot]]) form in the predominantly the leg or, more unusually, the arm.  The clot may break free from the venous wall and and travel via the [[circulatory system]] to the [[heart]] or to the [[lung|lungs]] (causing a [[pulmonary embolism]]); this condition is often caused by keeping the legs bent for long periods but can also be caused by other medical problems.

====Abbreviation====
*[[DVT]]

====Synonyms====
*'''deep venous thrombosis'''
*[[economy class syndrome]]

